  "body": "# Bug Report\n\n## Problem\n\nWhen updating account from it's settings in Wallet (Name/Colour) there is no way to apply the changes because `Apply` button is not showing up at the top-right of top-bar when changing any setting of the account. \n\n\n#### Expected behavior\n\nApply button appears at the top-right of the screen upon changin any of colour/name of \"Wallet\"-> \"Account\"-> \"Account settings\"\n#### Actual behavior\n<img width=\"280\" alt=\"Screenshot 2019-12-23 at 13 14 15\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/71355000-50394f80-2586-11ea-9836-79b06e18e554.png\">\n\n\n#### Notes\n\nFor the developer who will be investigating. Is it related to another PR? Tips on where to start? \n\n#### Acceptance Criteria\n\nMight be regression from https://github.com/status-im/status-react/commit/f90fe2f04ddd8fa8abc15eb2cb2c0af99837587a\n\n### Reproduction\n\n- Open Status and create new account\n- Navigate to `Wallet` -> `Status account` -> top-right `...` menu -> `Account settings`\n- Change name or colour\n\n### Additional Information\n\n- Status version: 0.14.0 (2019122015)\n- Operating System: Android and iOS",
